articles.description: David Collette scored 18 points on 9-of-10 shooting in a dominant performance around the paint and led Utah to a 77-43 win over California on Saturday night.
articles.headline: Utah dominates California for 77-43 win

articles.description: Rui Hachimura scored 23 points and No. 12 Gonzaga kept the ball out of Jock Landale's hands to end the nation's longest active winning streak at 19 games with a 78-65 victory over No. 11 Saint Mary's on Saturday night.
articles.headline: Gonzaga snaps Saint Mary's 19-game win streak, 78-65

images.caption: Rui Hachimura gets past three St. Mary's defenders and hits a tricky layup for a chance at a 3-point play.
images.name: Gonzaga's Hachimura scores tough basket for and-1

videos.description: Alex O'Connell finds Marvin Bagley III who hits a 3-point jumper for Duke.
videos.headline: Bagley drains corner 3

videos.description: Marvin Bagley III intercepts Utah Valley's basketball and takes it to the rim.
videos.headline: Duke's Bagley makes sweet left-handed dunk

videos.description: Grayson Allen scores his first points for Duke with a dunk followed by a nice 3-point jumper.
videos.headline: Allen comes alive with dunk and 3-pointer

videos.description: Grayson Allen tosses to Marvin Bagley III who makes a nice two-handed dunk in the second half.
videos.headline: Bagley finishes lob from Allen with slam dunk

videos.description: Shane Battier returns to the Blue Devil's arena to celebrate Mike Krzyzewski's 1,000th win as head coach at Duke.
videos.headline: Battier congratulates Coach K on 1,000 wins at Duke

videos.description: Mike Krzyzewski wins his 1,000th game as Duke head coach. He acknowledges fans, players and family after the Blue Devils' victory over Utah Valley on Saturday night.
videos.headline: Coach K: 'I am the luckiest guy to coach ever'
